  "texts": [
    "• Nannofossils: This group includes various types of microscopic algae, such as coccolithophores, which produce calcite plates called coccoliths.",
    "Nannofossils are important in marine biostratigraphy due to their abundance, rapid evolution, and widespread distribution.",
    "Their calcite structures are often well-preserved, and can provide critical information about past oceanic conditions (Agnini et al. 2006).",
    "• Conodonts: Conodonts are the fossilized remains of tooth-like structures (elements) that belonged to an extinct group of vertebrates.",
    "These fossils are composed of hydroxylapatite, a phosphate mineral, and are crucial for correlating and dating Palaeozoic strata."
  ],
